Ad Text:
What's the role?

Reporting to the Head of FP&A, this highly visible role plays a critical part in leading the organisation’s planning and reporting cycle for NCA. Acting as the key link between business partnering teams and executive leadership, you will consolidate insights across the business and translate financial results into clear, compelling narratives that drive commercial decision-making. You will be responsible for delivering high-quality internal and external reporting to senior stakeholders across News Corp Australia and Global Head Office (NY), providing strategic insights that create value and support enterprise-wide performance. Collaboration will be central to your success, as you work closely with commercial finance teams to understand all areas of the business and distil complex information into meaningful, actionable outcomes.

Responsibilities

Craft the ‘narrative’ of NCA’s results by analysing performance trends and drivers, explaining variances against budget and forecast, and influencing how these are communicated to the Executive Leadership Team and Global Head Office in NY.

Advise the ELT and Finance & Strategy Committee on macro-level decisions, including brand profitability assessments and setting cost/stretch targets.

Synthesise financial and commercial insights across all business units to forecast NCA-wide impacts, including understanding the business from NY’s point of view.

Deliver ad-hoc financial analysis and reporting for internal and external stakeholders.

Act as the subject matter expert and primary liaison with the Systems & Data team on system-related projects and maintaining the integrity of key FP&A systems.

Drive continuous process improvement, automation, and reporting standardisation to build a best-practice finance function.

Who are you?

Relevant experience in a similar FP&A or commercial finance role, with post-graduate qualifications (e.g., CA/CPA/CFA).

Effective communicator with strong attention to detail.

Strong commercial acumen and the ability to translate financial results into clear business narratives and actionable insights.

Able to convey the bigger picture while understanding the supporting detail.

Collaborative, building strong partnerships across teams to achieve shared objectives.

A self-starter who drives initiatives and takes accountability for outcomes.

Strong stakeholder engagement and project management skills.

Proficient in Google Sheets and Google Slides; experience with TM1 (IBM Planning Analytics Workspace) or similar systems is advantageous.

News Benefits

News Benefits is our way of saying thank you to our people for their valued contribution to News, our audiences, clients and communities. Thanking them for the great things they do daily, for the greater good of Australia. Our benefits include:

Exclusively ours - Access to publications and products from across the News Corp family

Health & wellbeing - Advice, support and facilities for healthy minds and bodies (including an onsite gym at our Adelaide, Brisbane & Sydney offices) 

Time off - News offers a range of leave options to support your personal needs and moments that matter in life: Parental leave, Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Career break and Compassionate leave.

Helping you grow - Development opportunities (including diversity and inclusion - focused education series) and recognition

Financial wellbeing - Support on making the most of your money

Perks & discounts - Exclusive offers across a range of products and services

Giving back - Make a difference to our communities.

Workplace Inclusion and facilities – Engage with your passions through various employee-resource groups and accessibility to multi-faith quiet rooms & parents’ rooms

Who are we?

News Corp Australia is the nation’s most influential media organisation, operating more than 150 household-name brands across print, digital and multimedia. We lead the way in travel, fashion, food, health, homes and lifestyle, and we are the largest publisher across print and digital, reaching more than 16 million Australians each month.

What’s next?

Apply now or for more information on careers at News Corp Australia visit www.newscorpaustralia.com/careers

Our Commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion We know that diversity strengthens our teams and newsrooms as we seek to tell stories that represent the diverse communities of Australia that we serve. Our people make us unique and we all have a story. We encourage people of all ages, backgrounds, races, cultures, religions, sexual orientations, abilities and gender identities to apply. Inclusion is important to us and we want everyone at News to bring their whole-selves to work. If you require any accommodations or adjustments throughout the recruitment process, or would like to outline which pronouns you prefer, please feel free to let us know.

For 37 consecutive years, we’ve been Australia’s leading truck brand, built on a foundation of reliability, innovation, and a workplace culture that consistently ranks among the best for employee engagement. Our leadership in the market is backed by decades of experience, a strong national network, and exceptional service support.

Our product range spans light to heavy duty trucks, featuring advanced engine technology and comprehensive safety systems. We proudly market, distribute, and support Isuzu Trucks and Isuzu Power Solutions across Australia.

Isuzu Australia Limited (IAL) has announced the establishment of a new finance and leasing company, Isuzu Financial Services Australia (IFSA). With operations scheduled to commence in the third quarter of 2026, this is a new joint initiative between IAL and Tokyo Century Corporation (TCC). The establishment of IFSA forms part of the broader strategy focusing on strengthening existing operations and expanding its product and service offering.

This is a rare opportunity to play a early part in building and shaping a national captive finance business from inception: designing robust credit frameworks, setting portfolio guardrails, and balancing strong commercial growth with disciplined risk management.




About the Role

We are seeking an experienced and commercially astute Senior Credit Analyst to provide hands-on commercial, SME and fleet credit expertise during IFSA’s growth and build phase.

Reporting to the Head of Credit & Risk, you will focus on quality credit decisioning, portfolio risk management, and the design and governance of digitised and automated credit frameworks. You will play a critical role in ensuring IFSA achieves strong commercial outcomes while maintaining prudent risk discipline. You will also act as a key senior credit interface with our joint venture partner, Tokyo Century, ensuring alignment on risk appetite, delegated authorities, governance standards, and portfolio performance.

Commercial, SME & Fleet Credit Assessment:

Assess and approve commercial, SME and fleet credit applications

Analyse financial statements, cash flow, serviceability and transaction structures
Provide clear, well-documented credit recommendations, conditions and risk mitigants

Deliver timely, consistent and commercially balanced credit decisions

Digitised & Automated Credit Decisioning:

Design and govern digitised and automated credit decisioning frameworks

Define automation rules, thresholds and escalation parameters

Monitor model performance, overrides and alignment to risk appetite

Contribute to continuous improvement of credit systems and workflow tools

Fleet Credit Limits & Portfolio Risk Management:

Establish and manage fleet credit limits and concentration exposures

Support portfolio monitoring, stress testing and risk reporting activities

Identify emerging risks and recommend mitigation strategies

Escalate material credit, model or portfolio risks in line with governance frameworks

Joint Venture & Stakeholder Engagement:

Act as the senior credit interface with Tokyo Century

Align on risk appetite, delegated authorities and portfolio performance metrics

Prepare and present credit insights for JV and executive forums

Engage effectively with Sales, Operations, Legal, Compliance, Product and Executive stakeholders




About You

To be successful in this role, ideally you will have the following skills and experience:

Demonstrated experience in digitised and automated lending environments, including setting credit rules, thresholds and escalation standards

Experience in asset finance, leasing or commercial vehicle finance (highly desirable)

Strong commercial credit judgement with the ability to assess complex SME, fleet and structured transactions pragmatically and defensibly

Advanced financial analysis capability, including interpretation of financial statements, cash flow and serviceability metrics

Strong portfolio risk management capability, including concentration risk and early-warning indicators

Bachelor’s degree in Business, Finance or a related discipline (preferred).

If you are commercially sharp, risk disciplined and motivated by building frameworks that will underpin long term portfolio quality, this is an opportunity to shape something from the ground up.




Why join Isuzu?

At Isuzu Australia, we don’t just lead the market, we lead with people. Joining Isuzu means becoming part of a globally recognised brand that is also Australia’s market leader. This is your opportunity to contribute to something bigger.

Market Leading Remuneration

Enjoy a competitive salary and generous financial benefits designed to recognise your contribution.

Wellbeing and Flexibility

Benefit from a hybrid work model, additional leave days, volunteer opportunities, and health and wellbeing initiatives that genuinely support work life balance.

Career Growth and Development

We invest in our people through structured learning programs, mentorship from experienced leaders, and a strong focus on internal promotion, giving you a clear pathway to progress.

Perks and Positive Culture

From a vibrant social club and monthly events to quarterly awards and interactive national meetings, we celebrate wins and celebrate each other. Our culture is not just words, it is why our people choose to stay.




We are proud to be an equal opportunity employer and value the unique perspectives each person brings. If you require any adjustments in the recruitment process such as alternative interview formats, assistive technology, or additional time, please let us know when you apply so we can support you.




Join us at Isuzu Australia and help keep Australia moving.

Drive your career forward with Australia’s #1 Truck Brand.

Job Title: Senior Business Intelligence Analyst | 12-month fixed term
Ad Text:
About Us

Founded nearly 40 years ago, Micromine is at the cutting edge of next-generation technology for mining. With offices around the world, we are one of the world's premier mining software companies; our technology is used in all corners of the globe.

 

What We Offer

An established multinational business, growing fast, with great benefits:

High growth company providing growth opportunities for our people
Work from home (WFH) and flexibility options to balance work and home life
12 weeks paid parental leave – primary and secondary carers
Free gym membership
Employee Assistance Program for you and your family
Social Connection and Responsibility Program
Discounted private health insurance
Novated leasing
The opportunity to work across both the Mining and Technology sectors
An engaging team culture and a modern office within Perth’s CBD

 

About The Opportunity

Micromine is continuing to invest in data and analytics capability across the business. This Senior Business Intelligence Analyst position is a 12-month fixed term maternity leave cover and will play a key role in delivering commercial insights and high-quality reporting that supports decision-making across sales, forecasting, and business performance.

This is a senior analytical role that requires more than operational reporting. You will be responsible for interrogating complex datasets, challenging assumptions, and translating data into meaningful commercial narratives for senior stakeholders.

Maintain and develop commercial reporting and analytics outputs using Power BI.
Work primarily with CRM and sales performance data sourced from NetSuite, with scope to support future integration of additional data sources.
Contribute to data transformation logic and analytics design thinking across multiple systems.
Produce executive-level reporting with clear commentary on key business performance drivers.
Perform rigorous sense-checking and validation of weekly sales, forecasting, and month-end reporting.
Engage with senior business stakeholders, including General Managers, to extract commercial insight that may not be visible in system data alone.
Challenge data quality and underlying assumptions where appropriate.
Support the ongoing development of automation and analytics capability across the business.

 

About You

You are a highly analytical professional with strong commercial judgement and exceptional attention to detail. You are comfortable working with imperfect data and can independently translate business questions into practical analytical solutions.

Other key skills, experience, and qualifications:

Experience delivering business intelligence and visual analytics solutions.
A strong understanding of back-end data considerations alongside front-end reporting.
The confidence to engage and challenge senior stakeholders.
The ability to think conceptually about analytics execution rather than requiring detailed step-by-step instruction.
A finance, commercial, or data analytics background is highly desirable.




Next Steps

If you are looking to shape the future direction of technology in the industry, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.

To learn more or apply, visit our website at www.micromine.com.

Micromine is dedicated to fostering a diverse and inclusive work environment, and we welcome applicants from a variety of backgrounds to apply.

Principal Project Accountant/Analyst | State Government

This is a high-profile opportunity for a strategic financial leader to join a major State Government initiative focused on digital innovation and small business support. As the Principal Project Accountant/Analyst, you will act as the financial backbone for a key departmental project, taking full ownership of end-to-end financial management to ensure sustainable and transparent delivery. You will work at the intersection of corporate finance and project delivery, providing the high-level analysis and robust frameworks necessary to translate complex data into actionable executive insights.

In this role, you will be expected to identify financial risks early and develop proactive mitigation strategies to keep project expenditure strictly aligned with the approved pipeline. You will lead the charge in creating detailed costing models and accurate forecasts that directly influence the department's strategic direction. If you are a seasoned professional who thrives in a collaborative, fast-paced government environment, this role offers the platform to showcase your expertise in fiscal oversight and contract management.

Key Responsibilities

Comprehensive Financial Oversight: Manage and contribute to the end-to-end delivery of project accounting services, including budgeting, financial management, and performance reporting.

Core Technical Delivery: Demonstrate expert-level proficiency in budgeting, forecasting, and reporting, alongside comprehensive general project accounting duties to support the project lifecycle.

Advanced Financial Modelling: Develop high-quality, detailed costing models and accurate forecasts to underpin informed decision-making across the project.

Executive Briefing & Reporting: Prepare sophisticated financial reports, briefing materials, and formal submissions for presentation to program boards and senior executive leadership.

Commercial Analysis & Tendering: Lead financial analysis and provide expert support for tender and bid evaluations, while overseeing contract management and monitoring vendor financial performance.

Stakeholder Management: Build and maintain collaborative, constructive relationships with internal clients and stakeholders to resolve emergent financial issues.

Regulatory Compliance: Ensure all project financial activities remain fully compliant with the Queensland Government financial management frameworks and standards.

Leadership & Team Culture: Promote a workplace culture of equity, diversity, and inclusion while proactively managing the performance and conduct of your staff.

Position Requirements

Government Experience: Previous experience working within a government environment is strictly required for this role to ensure a deep understanding of public sector financial frameworks.

Technical Mastery: Candidates must demonstrate a strong background in budgeting, forecasting, and reporting within a project-based environment.

Position Details

Contract: 12-Month Initial contract with a high possibility of extension.

Location: CBD-based with flexible Hybrid working arrangements.

Contact: For a confidential discussion or more information, please contact jack.coleman@randstad.com.au.

At Randstad, we are passionate about providing equal employment opportunities and embracing diversity to the benefit of all. We actively encourage applications from any background.

Job Title: Digital & Data - Strategy, Commercial and Portfolio Lead
Ad Text:
Transform lives, every single day

Do you want a career that means more? At Anglicare Sydney, we bring the strength, the support and the strategy to make it happen. We're a well-respected not-for-profit that's been serving society's most vulnerable for more than 160 years. Each year, we achieve life-changing outcomes for the 40,000+ people who rely on our person-centred support. And now, we're extending our reach and impact even further.

The rapid acceleration of data, digital and AI across Anglicare is mission critical to revolutionising how we serve our diverse and vulnerable communities. This role is for a commercial, highly strategic self-starter who can translate complexity into direction, build alignment across stakeholders, and help the organisation focus on what matters most.

Your opportunity

Reporting to the GM, Data & Digital, you'll act as a strategic "engine room" across the Digital & Data portfolio - a high-trust, high-impact role that brings structure, momentum and commercial sharpness to a fast-moving environment.

You'll take complex inputs from meetings, projects and stakeholders, connect the dots, and turn them into crisp executive-ready outputs that drive decisions and delivery. You'll also help create a consistent operating rhythm across initiatives - clarifying priorities, sequencing, governance and ways of working.

With integrity and resilience, you will:

Translate Digital & Data strategy into tangible artefacts:roadmaps, playbooks, governance rhythms, role clarity and decision pathways
Maintain a "single source of truth" across priorities, interdependencies and ways of working
Build and refine business cases, investment decks and strategic documents, including benefits, costs, risks and delivery approaches
Develop pragmatic sizing (ranges/scenarios/confidence levels) for value, effort and risk - with clear assumptions
Produce compelling executive materials (slides, memos, one-pagers) that drive clarity, consensus and action
Design and support executive/SBU sessions to align on priorities, trade-offs and sequencing
Create mechanisms that make engagement with Digital & Data easy: intake patterns, prioritisation forums and comms cadences
Partner across DigiTech, Finance, Strategy and SBUs to enable end-to-end outcomes and consistent narratives

What you'll bring

You're equal parts strategic, commercial and polished - someone who can move between ambiguity and action, and who's trusted to represent priorities clearly across senior stakeholders.

You'll likely bring:

A relevant degree (e.g., Commerce, Business Analytics, Computer Science or the Arts with relevant business experience)
3+ years in management consulting (strategy / operating model / transformation / digital advisory) within 5+ years broader experience
Demonstrated ability to produce executive-grade documentation (especially PowerPoint) and influence decisions
Strong commercial and analytical capability - benefits sizing, investment logic, options analysis, structured problem solving
The ability to turn complexity into crisp narratives: "why this, why now, what changes, how we'll measure it"
Confidence building pragmatic financial models and value cases (you don't need to be deeply technical)
Comfort with modern tooling for analysis and storytelling (Excel and PowerPoint is a must and Databricks/PowerBI /Canva/Figma a plus)
A collaborative influencing style - aligning people through clarity and story, not authority

Desirable (but not essential):

Digital/product exposure (discovery, agile delivery, service design)
Data/analytics/AI-adjacent strategy experience, portfolio governance and value tracking
Experience in complex service organisations (health, aged care, government, regulated environments)

Why Anglicare Sydney?

This is a chance to do genuinely meaningful work - and to have outsized impact in a role that shapes how a leading social impact organisation navigates change and opportunity. You'll be welcomed into a compassionate, respectful and purpose-driven community where we don't just talk about values - we live them.

At Anglicare, you'll get the security and stability of a strong, well-established organisation that's ready for the future - while working in a space (Digital, Data & AI) that's evolving quickly and creating new possibilities for mission impact.

You'll also enjoy:

Flexible work options to support work life balance
Salary packaging benefits to increase your take home pay - Up to $15,900 of your pay is tax free
Ongoing professional development and career growth opportunities
Access to wellbeing initiatives, discounts and employee support programs

Are you ready for a career that means more?

If you're a highly energetic change-maker motivated by driving meaningful impact for vulnerable people - and you thrive where strategic thinking, commercial clarity and executive storytelling meet - we'd love to hear from you.

Anglicare is as wonderfully diverse as the customers and communities we support. While guided by our Christian values, our team includes people of all faiths and backgrounds who share our commitment to serving others. We strongly encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, and people of all ages, genders, abilities and cultural backgrounds.

FOREVER US

Step into the world of Forever New, where fashion meets innovation and every experience is designed to make it her moment. From our Melbourne beginnings over 20 years ago to more than 450 stores globally, Forever New continues to evolve - blending beautiful fashion with smart, scalable technology that supports our teams and delights our customers.

As we continue to grow and transform our retail and digital landscape, we’re looking for a Senior Business Analyst to play a critical role in shaping the systems and processes that power our stores, supply chain, and digital channels.

THE PERKS WE OFFER YOU

As part of the Forever New family, you’ll enjoy benefits designed to support your success and wellbeing:

Generous 40% staff discount, plus family and friends’ discounts
Subsidised daily coffee and lunch at our on-site cafe
Subsidised parking at our vibrant Richmond Head Office
Loyalty and birthday leave to celebrate life’s milestones
Referral incentives for introducing great talent to our team
Access to wellbeing and sustainability initiatives
Continuous learning and development opportunities
Recognition through reward and service awards programs
Exposure to a global retail and technology environment

YOUR DREAM OPPORTUNITY

As the Senior Business Analyst, you’ll be responsible for ensuring our retail systems and processes effectively support business operations and customer outcomes. Reporting to the Digital Solutions Manager, you’ll work closely with stakeholders across stores, supply chain, head office, and technology teams to translate business needs into clear, practical, and high-quality technology solutions.

This is a hands-on, end-to-end role where you’ll influence how our POS, WMS, ERP, and merchandising platforms evolve - driving efficiency, data accuracy, and continuous improvement across the business.

GET EXCITED TO:

Lead end-to-end business analysis activities across retail, store operations, supply chain, and digital channels
Gather, analyse, and document business requirements for core retail systems including POS, WMS, ERP, and planning platforms
Facilitate workshops, interviews, and process-mapping sessions with stakeholders across stores, head office, and distribution centres
Translate business needs into clear user stories, functional and non-functional requirements, and acceptance criteria
Map current-state and future-state processes to identify gaps, inefficiencies, and improvement opportunities
Partner with technical teams to support solution design and ensure alignment with business and operational realities
Support system implementations, upgrades, and integrations across retail technology platforms
Develop and execute test plans, coordinate UAT, and validate solutions prior to deployment
Collaborate with vendors and third-party partners to clarify requirements, review deliverables, and ensure solution quality
Support change management activities including training materials, communications, and post-go-live support
Contribute to project planning, risk assessment, and prioritisation discussions
Maintain accurate documentation, process flows, and knowledge repositories
Drive continuous improvement by identifying and addressing technical debt

THE SKILLS & EXPERIENCE YOU OFFER US

Minimum 7 years of experience in IT, including proven success as a Business Analyst for at least 3+ years within mid-sized retail organizations.
Demonstrated expertise in leading business analysis for the implementation or replacement of core retail systems, including WMS, ERP platforms, POS, and Merchandising/Planning solutions. Omnichannel projects are desirable.
In-depth understanding of retail operations, store processes, and POS environments, with a focus on improving efficiency and customer experience.
Track record of delivering IT projects in fast-paced, dynamic environments with cross-functional teams.
Advanced analytical and problem-solving skills, with strong attention to detail and a commitment to quality documentation.
Proficient in business process mapping and modelling using tools such as Microsoft Visio and Lucidchart.
Skilled in Agile delivery frameworks and MoSCoW prioritization techniques, and collaboration tools including Jira and Confluence.
Exceptional communication and stakeholder engagement abilities, with the capacity to influence and align diverse teams.
Experience leading end-to-end business analysis across multiple projects while supporting BAU.
Adept at facilitating workshops, conducting stakeholder interviews, and defining future-state solutions through process mapping and requirements gathering.
Capable of producing comprehensive documentation including user stories, functional and non-functional specifications, business rules, schema mappings, and process flows.
Contributed to small-scale project delivery with opportunities to assume project management responsibilities.
Provide mentorship and oversight to peers, promoting consistency and adherence to best-practice standards.
Developed and executed test strategies, coordinated user acceptance testing (UAT), and ensured solutions met defined acceptance criteria.
Supported change management efforts including training development, communication planning, and post-implementation support.
Actively participated in project planning, risk assessment, and solution design to ensure alignment with business goals.

BEHAVIOURS & ATTRIBUTES

Strong analytical and problem-solving capability
Collaborative and relationship-focused, with excellent stakeholder engagement skills
Results-driven, with the ability to prioritise and deliver to deadlines
Calm, adaptable, and resilient under pressure
Clear and confident communicator, both written and verbal
Proactive mindset with a passion for continuous improvement

OUR VALUES

Everything we do at Forever New is guided by our values:
Think Customer
Respect for All
Keep it Simple
Take Responsibility
Act with Pace

Join Forever New and play a key role in shaping the technology and processes that support our people, our customers, and our continued global growth

Ad Text:
Based at either our Melbourne Burwood or Geelong Waterfront Campus, hybrid work available 
Fulltime and continuing

 

Do you want to lead the engineering of data and insights that shape strategic decision-making?

Deakin is seeking a Lead, Business Intelligence Data Engineering to oversee the design, development and operation of enterprise data engineering platforms that power high-quality analytics, reporting and insight-driven decision-making across the University.

This is a leadership role where technology, strategy and customer experience come together — enabling data to be trusted, accessible and meaningful for students, staff and researchers.

 

Why work with us?

At Deakin University, you’ll find more than a job - you’ll find a community and a way of working that supports you to do your best work. Across our campuses in Geelong, Melbourne and regional Victoria, we offer an environment designed to help you thrive, with on-site childcare, gyms, medical centres, cafés, accessible public transport and convenient parking.

We support flexible and hybrid working, generous leave provisions - including extended parental leave and the option to purchase additional leave - and a wide range of staff benefits and discounts. Combined with our strong focus on health, wellbeing and professional development, Deakin offers a supportive, inclusive culture where leaders are trusted, people are valued and careers can grow.

 

About the role

Deakin isn't just adopting AI – we're building it. With Deakin GEM now live and our AI Factory, a multi disciplinary AI squad, accelerating capability across the institution, ambitious work is underway across multiple streams.

As Lead, Business Intelligence Data Engineering you will lead the evolution of Deakin’s data engineering environment, ensuring robust, secure and scalable data platforms support organisational priorities. You will play a key role in delivering automated, high-quality data pipelines, improving data processing efficiency and strengthening enterprise business intelligence capability.

This role blends technical leadership with people leadership — fostering innovation, operational excellence and continuous improvement across data engineering practices.

Come and join us to transform data into intelligent insights that drive decisions. We need a Data Engineer who can build robust BI pipelines and infuse them with AI, from predictive analytics to LLM-powered exploration and creating data products that empower business users to ask smarter questions and get better answers.

You will:

Lead the design, development and maintenance of enterprise data engineering platforms and tools
Ensure data quality, security and governance standards are embedded across the enterprise data warehouse environment
Drive automation of data workflows to support scalable, efficient data processing
Oversee end-to-end data pipeline delivery across ingestion, transformation and serving layers
Lead capability improvement initiatives and evaluate emerging data technologies
Coach and inspire team members to deliver high-quality data engineering outcomes
Translate business requirements into effective, practical data solutions
Engage stakeholders to communicate the value of insights and support evidence-based decision-making

 

About you

You are an experienced data engineering or business intelligence leader who thrives in complex, enterprise environments. Most importantly, you are passionate about using data to create meaningful outcomes and empowering others to succeed.

You’ll bring:

Postgraduate qualifications or extensive relevant experience

About the Department

The Department of Health, Disability and Ageing leads national policy and programs that support the health, wellbeing and independence of Australians.

Working across health, aged care and disability reform, the Department partners with governments, providers and communities to deliver accessible, person-centred services and strengthen Australia's care systems for the future.

About the Role

One labour hire contractor is being sought to review, evaluate and provide advice regarding changes to aged care provider financial reporting in the Quarterly Financial Report (QFR) and Aged Care Financial Report (ACFR) data collections.

The role will work as part of a small team to review and recommend future changes to the QFR and ACFR data collections to ensure they are collecting fit-for-purpose data for changing policy and programs whilst also trying to streamline reporting and reduce the administrative burden of financial reporting for aged care providers. The role will also be required to design a multi-dimensional chart of accounts for the QFR and ACFR to manage the flow of data through the department's IT systems.

We require a highly skilled candidate who can quickly understand the intricacies of aged care provider financial reporting and provide advice regarding changes to the financial reporting. The candidates will hold Certified Practicing Accountant (CPA) or Chartered Accountant (CA) credentials or hold an accounting/finance degree or qualification. Experience in health/aged care sector financial reporting is also highly desirable.

Key Duties

Provide specialist analysis and advice on aged care provider financial reporting matters.
Propose, analyse and assess requests for changes to the QFR and ACFR data collections and definitions, adhering to prescribed Principles and Drivers.
Develop and update templates, resources and guidance materials to support aged care providers meeting their financial reporting responsibilities.
Lead the preparation of briefing materials and presentations to support consultation with stakeholders and advice to Senior Executives as decision makers.
Lead stakeholder engagement with aged care providers, teams across the Ageing and Aged Care Group, the Independent Health and Aged Care Pricing Authority and the Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission.
Coordinating work activities including planning, scheduling, reporting and managing risks as appropriate.

Required Capabilities

Specialist technical accounting / financial reporting capability, including the ability to undertake analysis and provide advice regarding financial data and reporting matters.
Strong stakeholder management, interpersonal and communication skills, including the ability to build and maintain effective working relationships with internal and external stakeholders.
Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to provide succinct and accurate technical advice.
Ability to work independently under limited direction, respond flexibly to change, think critically, analyse and solve complex problems and make decisions using research and analysis, good judgement, expertise and knowledge.
Demonstrates strong attention to detail, ensuring accuracy and consistency in all tasks and documentation.
Demonstrated planning and organisational skills, including ability to meet deadlines with competing priorities in a complex, changing and high-pressure environment.

About CTM 
CTM is a global award-winning provider of innovative and cost-effective travel management solutions to the corporate, events, leisure and loyalty travel markets. CTM provides personalised service excellence with client-facing technology solutions in offices all around the world, including New Zealand, Australia, Asia, North America and Europe with over 3000 employees.
  
At CTM, our people are our greatest asset. We are a team of collaborative, innovative and future focused professionals we work with the company's values in mind; Connect, Deliver and Evolve.

About the Role 
The purpose of the role is to provide leadership, oversight and governance to design, govern and oversee the implementation of data standards and integrity of CTM's data assets across all global and regional operations.
 
The role ensures that data used for decision-making, reporting and customer engagement is consistent and trusted. It establishes and maintains the frameworks, standards and controls that protect CTM's data assets and ensures alignment with internal assurance requirements.
 
As the global authority for data standards, this position promotes a culture of accountability and continuous improvement in data management practices. About us

FISHBOWL is one of Australia’s most trusted brands on a mission to change the culture around fast food. Founded in 2016 in Bondi, the brand has expanded to over 50 stores across Sydney, Melbourne, Brisbane, the Gold Coast, and more recently, New York. With our continued growth, our focus is now on elevating and refining all aspects of the brand, instilling a culture of excellence in our head office, and supporting our team in-store to deliver the best product and experience to our customers.




About the role

At FISHBOWL, we believe great decisions are powered by great data. This is a newly created, standalone Senior Commercial Analyst role reporting directly to the Chief Financial Officer.

You will own end-to-end FP&A across the group, covering budgeting, forecasting management reporting and commercial analysis for both our Australian operations and our growing presence in the US (currently three stores).




Skills and experience

This role requires a highly capable and commercially astute finance professional who combines strong technical modelling skills with sound judgement, intellectual curiosity, and exceptional attention to detail.

You’ll have:

5+ years’ experience in FP&A, commercial finance or a related role within a fast-paced, multi-site retail, FMCG or QSR environment, with increasing levels of responsibility

Demonstrated experience owning end-to-end budgeting and rolling forecast processes, including assumption setting and stakeholder alignment

Proven experience preparing Board-ready management reporting and executive-level presentations

Strong commercial acumen with the ability to interpret financial results in an operational context and translate insights into clear business implications

Exceptional attention to detail, with a rigorous quality-control mindset and a track record of delivering highly accurate outputs

High intellectual curiosity and a willingness to investigate and challenge when results do not “look right”

Advanced financial modelling capability (including scenario and sensitivity analysis) with expert-level Excel skills; experience with BI tools (e.g. Power BI) desirable

Strong written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to distil complex analysis into clear, actionable insights

Comfortable operating with significant autonomy in a lean environment

CA/CPA qualification advantageous

Management consulting or strategy experience desirable.




Responsibilities

The right candidate will bring a structured, hypothesis-led problem-solving approach - able to frame ambiguous business questions, break them into actionable components, and guide stakeholders toward clear, commercially sound decisions.

This role will initially carry full responsibility for the group's FP&A function and is suited to someone ready to operate at a senior level with significant autonomy and accountability. This is a highly visible role suited to someone who thrives in a fast-paced environment and takes accountability for outcomes.

You'll be expected to:

Budgets and forecasts:

Own and lead the annual budgeting process and rolling forecasts (e.g. 3+9), ensuring assumptions are commercially grounded and clearly documented

Develop robust scenario modelling and continuously refine forecasting methodologies o improve accuracy and reliability.

Commercial analysis and decision support:

Evaluate store, market, and product-level profitability, including detailed unit economics analysis

Translate financial data into practical, actionable insights for Operations, Marketing, HR, and other departments

Lead structured problem-solving initiatives on commercial questions (e.g. new store economics, pricing architecture, labour optimisation, real estate decision making), using a hypothesis-driven and data-backed approach

Proactively identify areas where performance gaps exist, diagnose root causes, and develop clear, prioritised action plans in partnership with stakeholders.

Management reporting and board support:

Deliver weekly flash P&L reporting with clear, concise commentary on trends, risks, and emerging issues

Lead monthly management and Board reporting, ensuring accuracy, clarity, and strong commercial insight

Process improvement and FP&A development:

Strengthen reporting processes, controls, and data integrity across the FP&A function

Improve the structure, usability, and impact of financial dashboards and reporting

Play a key role in shaping and scaling the finance function as the business grows.

Business Analysis, Requirements & Product Ownership

Translate business needs into clear functional requirements, process definitions, and system decision flows

Review system and AI outputs for correctness, robustness, and alignment with business expectations, controlling scope and preventing drift

Document current-state (“as-is”) processes and design future-state (“to-be”) workflows incorporating automation, AI-assisted steps, and improved controls

Ad Text:
Do you want your work to make a difference for NSW?

Working to protect the state’s environment and heritage.

 

If you are passionate about using advanced analytics to guide the energy transition and deliver long-term system resilience, we encourage you to apply.

 

Permanent Full-time (35 hours per week) opportunity
Based in Parramatta with hybrid working supported
Salary relative to experience, and ranges from $149,739 to $173,174 pa plus superannuation.

 

We are seeking a strategic and technically accomplished Manager, Energy Modelling and Analytics to lead the development and implementation of advanced energy data models and business intelligence capabilities for the NSW electricity and gas systems. This team is part of the Data & Analytics branch in Energy, Climate Change and Sustainability.

This is a leadership role responsible for shaping long-term energy policy through rigorous analytics, scenario modelling and evidence-based insights. The role will guide complex quantitative modelling, inform executive decision-making, and create an integrated, forward-looking view of energy supply, demand and pricing across NSW.

 

The role will also be responsible for:

Assessing short- and medium-term risks, including the impacts of policy proposals and technology disruption.
Lead the development of frameworks, standards and policies that strengthen organisational data capability and governance.
Maintaining up-to-date expertise in a rapidly evolving energy market shaped by legislative, regulatory and policy change.

 

Should you require further information about the role please contact Ben Cirulis, Director Data and Analytics via ben.cirulis@dcceew.nsw.gov.au.

 

About You

You are an experienced leader with expertise in energy systems modelling, quantitative analysis and strategic policy development.

You will have proven experience and knowledge of electricity markets and an understanding of the National Electricity Market and extensive experience with complicated data model languages and systems such as Python, MATLAB, R, SQL, PLEXOS etc. 

 

Additionally, you will bring a:

Strong background in energy market modelling (electricity and/or gas).
Advanced quantitative and analytical capability.
Experience leading multidisciplinary teams and complex projects.
Demonstrated ability to translate technical insights into clear executive advice.
Strong stakeholder management and communication skills.

 

Essential Requirements

Qualifications or relevant experience in mathematics/statistics or a related discipline

 

For more information read the full Role Description: Manager Energy Modelling & Analytics.docx

 

Who we are

The Department of Climate Change, Energy, the Environment and Water (DCCEEW) works to protect the state’s environment and heritage. It leads the way on climate change, driving the sustainable transition to a net zero economy, powered by affordable, reliable, and clean energy.

The Department’s Energy, Climate Change and Sustainability (ECCS) Group leads strategic policy, programs and major initiatives on climate change, renewable energy, energy reliability and affordability, environmental sustainability.

Role Purpose 

Reporting to the Senior IT Project Manager and implementing various IT & Data projects with a focus on Trading & Risk. Playing a pivotal part in ensuring that business requirements are defined, and IT & Data solutions/systems are implemented to deliver the business outcomes.

 

Key Responsibilities:

Participate in and/or lead multiple change initiatives up to $250k in value

Conduct interviews to gather user requirements and business benefits via workshops, questionnaires, surveys, workflow storyboards, report mock ups, use cases scenarios and data mapping.

Work with stakeholders, project, and technical teams to prioritize collected requirements, identify solutions and develop business cases.

Create ‘As is’ and ‘To Be’ business or technical process flows as required

Complete or update system documentation as required

Provide first line of support to the business for live systems, understanding user problems and working with technical teams to resolve.

Work/engage with UK teams as required

Prepare specifications for reports including data lineage and definitions

 

Performance Indicators:

Delivery of practical solutions that resolve business issues.

Solutions implemented within agreed scope, budget and timeframes, as well as in accordance with technical design standards & internal governance practices.

Stakeholder end of change or project surveys

 

Experience:

Experience in a Business/Technical Analyst role with experience on complex technology implementation projects

Experience developing and documenting business process maps, user stories and utilising MoSCoW methods (or equivalent) 

Experience working with third party software development organisations or inhouse development teams

Hands-on software development or design experience (optional)  

Strong analytical and structured way of thinking, high organizational skills and attention to detail

At least 5 years' experience, preferably working for 2 or more energy retailers

Can write basic SQL and/or Python to perform data testing  

Work with stakeholders at all levels in an organization

 

Knowledge:

Strong knowledge of wholesale energy markets, retail electricity supply market, regional sales markets as well as market rules and regulations.

Strong knowledge of ETRM systems ideally Energy One

Understanding of derivatives used on the over the counter (OTC) and Energy Futures market eg Caps, Swaps and how they are valued and settled

Knowledge of energy risk metrics like VAR, EAR and volumetric limits and how they are applied in an energy trading context 

Knowledge of grid scale batteries and the auto bidders used to optimization the asset and communicate with AEMO

Job Title: Senior Trust Manager – Debt & Securitisation Services
Ad Text:
An exciting opportunity at a tier 1 Corporate Trust business to lead the Trust Management Analytics and Modelling for complex securitisation transactions. As part of our clients Corporate Trustee Services team, you will play a key role in supporting the growth of our securitisation business and delivering exceptional outcomes for clients.

This position offers exposure to sophisticated deal structures, financial modelling, and stakeholder engagement in a dynamic and expanding market.

This role is a lead Trust Analytics / Trust Management SME role, seeking someone with strong financial modelling experience based on deal transaction documentation using Excel and  SecureHub, they will lead the Analytic and financial modelling function for the business.

About the Role

Manage securitisation and structured finance transactions from a trust management perspective.

Review deal transaction documents for compliance with operational requirements.

Update securitisation models using Servicer Report data and prepare and distribute monthly investor reports.

Prepare and distribute RBA Repo reporting for eligible securities.

Maintain bond registers and ledgers as required.

Oversee client relationships and ensure trust management service levels are met.

Assist with new client onboarding and review deal transaction documentation from a trust management perspective.

Build and maintain financial models based on deal transaction documentation using Excel and SecureHub.

Contribute to process improvements and participate in ad hoc projects.

What You Need

Bachelor’s degree with at least 5 years of relevant Corporate Trust or other financial services industry experience. 

Experience with servicing the securitisation market from a trust management perspective would be well-regarded.

Being numerate, having good attention to detail, being able to organise time to complete required tasks, being client-focused and having a positive can-do attitude are essential for this role.

Proven record in the building and running of financial models.

Ability to work with team members located in various geographic locations.

Good written and verbal communication skills with a commitment to ensuring a positive, calm, respectful and harmonious workplace

EA 13 – 38 Hours
$140,108.04 + Super
Monthly RDO

You will be responsible for supporting the delivery of high quality, integrated growth servicing planning by collating and validating growth data, conducting analysis and producing growth forecasts and intelligence to inform strategic decision making.

What you will be doing 

Undertake detailed spatial analyses to produce growth forecasts and market intelligence for Sydney Water planning and investment decisions.
Analyse and interpret data from a range of sources including planning proposals, development applications, market intelligence, land use rezoning and government strategies/plans to produce meaningful intelligence.
Manage and maintain GIS datasets to ensure data accuracy and consistency using a range of spatial and data management tools.
Monitor external trends in population, policy, urban form, growth and economic development and their impact on growth planning.
Participate in government and stakeholder engagement to promote Sydney Water’s strategic direction on liveability, affordability and resilience for customers and communities in line with strategy.

About you 

Relevant tertiary qualification (e.g. Spatial/Geographical Information Systems, Spatial Science, Urban Planning, Geography or related discipline) or experience deemed equivalent.
Proven experience in the preparation of spatial and graphical outputs using GIS platforms, statistical tools, spreadsheets and data visualisation and/or transformation tools.
Demonstrated knowledge of urban planning processes, development servicing and growth intelligence with the ability to apply this understanding directly to growth forecasting.
Strong analytical skills to identify issues, trends, drivers and links to customer/ regulatory needs.

Category: Corporate Finance & Investment Banking (Banking & Financial Services)
Ad Text:
About the business

Our client is a specialist Australian real estate private credit and investment manager with a strong and growing footprint in land development and real assets. Their property arm focuses on the acquisition, feasibility, structuring and delivery of large-scale residential and mixed-use projects across Australia.

As their development pipeline continues to expand, they are seeking a highly analytical Investment Analyst to support investment and development decisions through best-in-class financial modelling and commercial analysis.

The opportunity

You will sit at the heart of the investment and development decision-making process, building and refining complex 3-way financial models that assess project feasibilities, returns, funding structures and risk scenarios.

Your work will directly influence which projects proceed, how they are structured, and how capital is deployed. This is not a reporting or month-end role – it is a commercial, forward-looking and decision-facing position. If you enjoy working in Excel, solving complex problems and seeing your analysis translate into real-world outcomes, this will be right up your alley.

Key responsibilities
Build, maintain and enhance detailed 3-way financial models (P&L, cash flow, balance sheet)
Develop land development feasibilities and investment models
Support acquisition underwriting and project evaluation
Perform sensitivity analysis, scenario modelling and stress testing
Analyse funding structures, returns and project economics
Assist with investment papers, board materials and decision packs
Continuously improve modelling frameworks and assumptions
Provide commercial insights to senior stakeholders
About you

You may come from a background such as:

Investment analysis
Corporate finance / transaction services / advisory
Development feasibilities or property analysis
Infrastructure or project finance
Valuations or modelling teams
You will ideally have:

Advanced Excel skills (essential)
Strong experience building 3-way models from scratch
A highly analytical and logical mindset
A degree in Finance, Economics, Mathematics, Engineering or similar
Strong attention to detail
The ability to translate numbers into clear commercial insights
Why this role?
High-impact, decision-facing position
Exposure to real capital deployment and development projects
Strong learning curve and career progression
Work closely with senior investment and development leaders

CAE Overview

At CAE, we equip people in critical roles with the expertise and solutions to create a safer world. As a technology company, we digitalize the physical world, deploying software-based simulation training and critical operations support solutions. Above all else, we empower pilots, cabin crew, airlines, and defence and security forces to perform at their best every day and when the stakes are the highest. Around the globe, we’re everywhere customers need us to be with more than 13,000 employees in approximately 250 sites and training locations in over 40 countries. CAE represents more than 75 years of industry firsts—the highest-fidelity flight and mission simulators as well as training programs powered by digital technologies. We embed sustainability in everything we do. Today and tomorrow, we’ll make sure our customers are ready for the moments that matter.

Overview

This is an exciting opportunity for a Senior Financial Analyst who likes to be hands-on, drive improvement through analytics and work collaboratively with the business. In this role, you will own forecasting, budgeting, reporting, and providing insights that help drive the organisation’s growth. You will deliver insightful analysis, constructive challenges, and clear visibility into business performance, forecasting and operational drivers.

This role will be hired a full time, 6-month fixed term contract (Parental Leave Cover).

The role we are offering you

Lead the end-to-end monthly forecasting cycle, ensuring accuracy, timeliness and alignment with business expectations.

Drive the annual budgeting process, coordinating inputs across departments and ensuring alignment with strategic and financial objectives.

Own cash flow forecasting and working capital management.

Coordinate and consolidate financial data across the IPAC region, ensuring accuracy.

Our ideal candidate has:

Extensive experience in FP&A, corporate finance or business partnering

Hands-on experience with ERP and BI systems

Can showcase strong analytical and problem-solving skills

Proven experience presenting financial information to senior management and influencing business decisions

Location:

Homebush, NSW

We operate a hybrid working approach.

What CAE offers you:

Opportunity to make a positive impact on Australian defence and security

Exciting career paths in a truly global business

Access to a generous ADF Reserve Service Policy

Security requirements

As the Australian Department of Defence is a major client, you must be eligible to obtain a Defence Security Clearance to work in this role – please be mindful to obtain a clearance, one of the main requirements is you must be an Australian Citizen.

Applications

If this role fits what you are looking for and you believe you have the necessary skills and experience, click ‘Apply Now’ and attach your resume.
